Common.Strapline.Common.Text: BROOKVALE - OPEN PLAN OFFICE OFFERING FLEXIBLE SIZE RANGES

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE are proud to present an outstanding opportunity to position your business in the most prominent industrial precincts on the Northern Beaches.

114 Old Pittwater Road features a combination of modern office, warehouse & technical accommodation, situated on a large site with mature landscaping opposite Warringah Mall.

Located at the gateway to the Northern Beaches, Brookvale is surrounded by a diverse mix of commercial, industrial, retail and residential uses. It is the Central Hub of the Northern beaches located only 16kms from the CBD.

Brookvale is one of the strongest and most well established industrial precincts. It continues to develop as an essential part of Sydney offering a strong workforce and supporting amenity such as Warringah Mall and efficient transport links.

This property is a great opportunity for a company to relocate to the Northern Beaches most sought after business hub. With unrivalled amenity and lifestyle position occupiers in the estate enjoy an onsite café, Warringah Mall being a short stroll away and being moments to several of Sydney’s iconic beaches. 

On offer is flexible modern fitted office space with 680sqm to 2,767sqm approx. Available. The office has a generous parking allocation on with visitor car spaces also available. The property is surrounded by an abundance of government infrastructure investment including the completed B-line, Warringah Road underpass (recently completed) and Northern Beaches tunnel (under planning). Some of the other property features include;

-Flexible & Refurbished office areas 680sqm to 2,767sqm 
-Moments to Warringah Mall
-Onsite licenced café
-Gyms, Pilates and child care nearby
- Modern Fitted and non-fitted options, ready to move in
-Generous parking allocation 1:37
-Designated visitor parking
-Moment to iconic beaches

For more information on this opportunity please contact the exclusive agent Ben Byford, CBRE
